Paper Types for Digital Large-Format Printing



Digital large-format printing is really a professional procedure for printing in large sized material that were created through desktop publishing programs along with other digital means. Posters, banners, murals, and advertising signs are the most typical items that use this method. If you'd like to make use of this printing method, you need to know the different kinds of paper that you can use for this process. This will help you make professionally looking printed materials.

Prior to choosing your printing paper, one important thing you have to pay attention to is what type of document you need to create. You need to know how you will employ the document.

Bond paper and copy paper come in large sizes beginning with 11 inches by 17 inches. These kinds of paper vary in brightness and thickness. When the document's going to be displayed, lamination is usually done after printing to preserve the material because it can be simply ripped or damaged. Most people use the smaller variety of this paper for everyday documents.

Offset lithography papers, whether coated or uncoated, aren't advisable for regular- and large-format digital printing. Because of the high moisture content of this kind of paper, it winds up wrinkled when used for digital printing. Carbonless papers, however, are only able to be utilized for digital printing and never for other printing processes. Each unit contains encapsulated dyes, which are released when passed through the printer. This results in transferring the images from one sheet to a different.

