There are also all-purpose papers, which you can use for all types of printers including digital, offset and inkjet. You may also utilize them for copiers and fax machines and copiers. Additionally they are available in wide sizes for printing materials in large format.

Rag bonds and recycled papers are more expensive when compared to a printing papers. Rag bonds are made from a combination of wood and cotton fibers. Recycled papers will come from post-consumer or industrial waste. Since both these types of paper goods are textured, many people include the paper's surface included in the overall design.

Prints that are needed to be placed on window, walls, posts, and other surfaces to ensure they are look like murals use self-adhesive photo papers. They come in outdoor and indoor types. The best ones absorb the digital printer properly and can be also removed and repositioned.

Should you need digital large-format printing for your next project, be sure you know which paper to make use of so you can get the best results.